Introduction

GG, formerly known as PoshGirls is an independent three-member girl group. Originally as eight, they made their debut on August 18, 2021, with the mini album "S.O.G: Songs Of Goddess".

Their name is a compound word of the words 'Posh' meaning elegant and 'Girls', and has the meaning of elegant girls singing hopes and dreams. The group initially disbanded on March 1, 2023, due to company management issues making it hard to operate.
